==DFB-Pokal==
{{main|2014–15 DFB-Pokal}}

===DFB-Pokal review===
The draw for the first round of the [[2014–15 DFB-Pokal|DFB-Pokal]] was held on 1 June.<ref name="Zwei Drittligisten für Bayern und Dortmund">{{cite news|title=Zwei Drittligisten für Bayern und Dortmund|url=http://www.sueddeutsche.de/sport/auslosung-dfb-pokal-zwei-drittligisten-fuer-bayern-und-dortmund-1.1981694|accessdate=1 June 2014|publisher=Süddeutsche Zeitung|date=1 June 2014|language=German}}</ref> Bayern were drawn against [[SC Preußen Münster|Preußen Münster]].<ref name="Zwei Drittligisten für Bayern und Dortmund"/> The match took place on 17 August.<ref name=rd1/> Bayern won 4–1 with goals from Mario Götze, Thomas Müller, David Alaba, and [[Claudio Pizarro]].<ref name=rd1/> [[Rogier Krohne]] scored for Preußen Münster.<ref name=rd1/> Robert Lewandowski failed to convert from the penalty spot in the last minute of the match.<ref>{{cite news|title=Badstuber lindert die Sorgen|url=http://www.sueddeutsche.de/sport/comeback-des-bayern-verteidigers-badstuber-lindert-die-sorgen-1.2093044|accessdate=19 August 2014|publisher=Süddeutsche Zeitung|date=18 August 2014|language=German}}</ref> Holger Badstuber played his first competitive match since getting injured<ref>{{cite news|title=SC Preußen Münster 1 4 Bayern Munich|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/0/football/28784333|accessdate=17 August 2014|publisher=BBC Sports|date=17 August 2014}}</ref> on 1 December 2012 against Borussia Dortmund.<ref name="Kroos und Götze machen das Remis klar"/> Bastian Schweinsteiger was unavailable for the match.<ref>{{cite news|title=Bayern-Trainer Guardiola fordert einen neuen Spieler|url=https://www.welt.de/sport/fussball/bundesliga/fc-bayern-muenchen/article131291118/Bayern-Trainer-Guardiola-fordert-einen-neuen-Spieler.html|accessdate=16 August 2014|publisher=Die Welt|date=16 August 2014|language=German}}</ref> Bayern were drawn against Hamburger SV in the second round draw.<ref>{{cite news|title=HSV trifft auf FC Bayern, BVB auf St. Pauli|url=http://www.sueddeutsche.de/sport/-runde-im-dfb-pokal-hsv-trifft-auf-den-fc-bayern-dortmund-auf-st-pauli-1.2100973|accessdate=23 August 2014|publisher=Süddeutsche Zeitung|date=23 August 2014|language=German}}</ref> The match took place on 29 October with Bayern winning 3–1.<ref name=rd2/> Robert Lewandowski, David Alaba, and Franck Ribéry scored for Bayern and [[Pierre-Michel Lasogga]] scored for Hamburg.<ref>{{cite news|title=Bayern machen mit schwachem HSV kurzen Prozess|url=https://www.welt.de/sport/fussball/bundesliga/fc-bayern-muenchen/article133794368/Bayern-machen-mit-schwachem-HSV-kurzen-Prozess.html|accessdate=29 October 2014|publisher=Die Welt|date=29 October 2014|language=German}}</ref> [[Jaroslav Drobný]] made several saves against Bayern.<ref>{{cite news|title=Pokal-Aus für den HSV: Lasogga trifft, Westermann patzt|url=http://www.mopo.de/spielberichte/1-3-gegen-bayern-pokal-aus-fuer-den-hsv--lasogga-trifft--westermann-patzt,5067100,28892706.html|accessdate=30 October 2014|publisher=[[Hamburger Morgenpost]]|date=29 October 2014|language=German}}</ref> Ribéry was hit by a spectator with a scarf<ref>{{cite news|title=Franck Ribery hit by scarf as Bayern Munich win in German Cup|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/0/football/29827942|accessdate=30 October 2014|publisher=BBC Sports|date=29 October 2014}}</ref> which Hamburg were eventually fined for.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Uersfeld|first1=Stephan|title=Hamburg fined for pitch invader attack on Bayern Munich's Franck Ribery|url=http://www.espnfc.com/german-bundesliga/story/2254717/hamburg-fined-for-pitch-invader-who-attacked-bayern-munich-franck-ribery|accessdate=20 January 2015|publisher=ESPN FC|date=20 January 2015}}</ref> Medhi Benatia was suspended for the match.<ref name="Altlasten aus Italien: Benatia im Pokal gesperrt"/> Bayern were drawn against [[Eintracht Braunschweig]] in the round of 16 draw.<ref>{{cite news|title=BVB trifft auf Dresden, Bayer auf Kaiserslautern|url=http://www.sueddeutsche.de/sport/achtelfinale-im-dfb-pokal-bvb-trifft-auf-dresden-bayer-auf-kaiserslautern-1.2198053|accessdate=30 October 2014|publisher=Süddeutsche Zeitung|date=30 October 2014|language=German}}</ref> The match took place on 4 March.<ref name=r16/> Bayern won 2–0 with two goals from David Alaba and Mario Götze.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Warmbrunn|first1=Benedikt|title=Humorlos gegen alle Gesetze|url=http://www.sueddeutsche.de/sport/pokal-erfolg-des-fc-bayern-humorlos-gegen-alle-gesetze-1.2378771|accessdate=4 March 2015|publisher=Süddeutsche Zeitung|date=4 March 2015|language=German}}</ref> Alaba scored in stoppage time in the first half<ref name="Erst Alabas Traumtor knackt Braunschweigs Abwehr">{{cite news|title=Erst Alabas Traumtor knackt Braunschweigs Abwehr|url=https://www.welt.de/sport/article138077544/Erst-Alabas-Traumtor-knackt-Braunschweigs-Abwehr.html|accessdate=4 March 2015|publisher=Die Welt|date=4 March 2015|language=German}}</ref> after Arjen Robben won a free kick<ref>{{cite news|title=Bayern Munich reach DFB-Pokal quarterfinals, Werder Bremen stunned|url=http://www.espnfc.com/german-dfb-pokal/story/2331849/bayern-cruise-to-reach-quarterfinals-of-dfb-pokalwerder-bremen-stunned|accessdate=4 March 2015|publisher=ESPN FC|date=4 March 2015}}</ref> and Götze scored in the 57th minute.<ref name="Erst Alabas Traumtor knackt Braunschweigs Abwehr"/> In the quarterfinal draw, Bayern were drawn against Bayer Leverkusen.<ref>{{cite news|title=Schweres Pokal-Los für Bayern, BVB mit mehr Glück|url=https://www.welt.de/sport/fussball/article138193220/Schweres-Pokal-Los-fuer-Bayern-BVB-mit-mehr-Glueck.html|accessdate=8 March 2015|publisher=Die Welt|date=8 March 2015|language=German}}</ref> The match took place on 8 April.<ref name=qf/> The match finished in a 0–0 draw with Bayern advancing after winning in a shoot-out 5–3.<ref name="Elfmeter oder nix">{{cite news|last1=Kneer|first1=Christof|title=Elfmeter oder nix|url=http://www.sueddeutsche.de/sport/fc-bayern-im-dfb-pokal-elfmeter-oder-nix-1.2426429|accessdate=8 April 2015|publisher=Süddeutsche Zeitung|date=8 April 2015|language=German}}</ref> Leverkusen's first kick was saved after [[Manuel Neuer]] "parried" [[Josip Drmić]]'s shot.<ref name="Elfmeter oder nix"/> Medhi Benatia left the match due to injury in the 34th minute.<ref>{{cite news|title=Benatia: "Falle zwei bis vier Wochen aus"|url=http://www.kicker.de/news/fussball/bundesliga/startseite/624752/artikel_benatia_falle-zwei-bis-vier-wochen-aus.html|accessdate=10 April 2015|publisher=kicker|date=9 April 2015|language=German}}</ref> In the semifinal draw, Bayern were drawn against Borussia Dortmund.<ref>{{cite news|title=Bayern empfängt den BVB, Wolfsburg in Bielefeld|url=https://www.welt.de/sport/fussball/article139288257/Bayern-empfaengt-den-BVB-Wolfsburg-in-Bielefeld.html|accessdate=9 April 2015|publisher=Die Welt|date=9 April 2015|language=German}}</ref> The match took place on 28 April.<ref name=sf/> The match finished in a 1–1 draw with Borussia Dortmund winning in a shoot-out.<ref name="Aus allen Träumen gerutscht">{{cite news|last1=Warmbrunn|first1=Benedikt|title=Aus allen Träumen gerutscht|url=http://www.sueddeutsche.de/sport/halbfinale-im-dfb-pokal-aus-allen-traeumen-gerutscht-1.2457674|accessdate=28 April 2015|publisher=Süddeutsche Zeitung|date=28 April 2015|language=German}}</ref> Bayern missed all four of their shots in the shoot-out.<ref name="Aus allen Träumen gerutscht"/> Borussia Dortmund converted two of their shots.<ref name="Dortmund reach cup final after Bayern miss all four penalties in shootout">{{cite news|title=Dortmund reach cup final after Bayern miss all four penalties in shootout|url=http://www.espnfc.us/german-dfb-pokal/match/418998/bayern-munich-borussia-dortmund/report|accessdate=28 April 2015|publisher=ESPN FC|date=28 April 2015}}</ref><ref name="Bayern Mun 1 1 Bor Dortmd">{{cite news|title=Bayern Mun 1 1 Bor Dortmd|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/0/football/32484226|accessdate=28 April 2015|publisher=BBC Sport|date=28 April 2015}}</ref> Robert Lewandowski scored in the 29th minute<ref name=sf/> and [[Pierre-Emerick Aubameyang]] scored in the 75th minute for Borussia Dortmund,<ref name="Dortmund reach cup final after Bayern miss all four penalties in shootout"/> three minutes after their first shot.<ref name="Bayern Mun 1 1 Bor Dortmd"/> Prior to Borussia Dortmund scoring, referee [[Peter Gagelmann]] denied Bayern a penalty shot.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Harding|first1=Jonathan|title=Dortmund beat Bayern in shoot-out drama to make German Cup final|url=http://www.dw.de/dortmund-beat-bayern-in-shoot-out-drama-to-make-german-cup-final/a-18416115|accessdate=28 April 2015|publisher=Deutsche Welle|date=28 April 2015}}</ref> Borussia Dortmund went down a man after [[Kevin Kampl]] was sent–off after receiving a second yellow card.<ref name="Bayern Mun 1 1 Bor Dortmd"/> Arjen Robben returned from injury, coming on as a substitute,<ref name=sf/> but left the match after 15 minutes with a calf injury, causing him to miss the rest of the season.<ref name="Rein und raus – der bittere Abend des Arjen Robben">{{cite news|last1=Flohr|first1=Sven|title=Rein und raus – der bittere Abend des Arjen Robben|url=https://www.welt.de/sport/fussball/bundesliga/fc-bayern-muenchen/article140240224/Rein-und-raus-der-bittere-Abend-des-Arjen-Robben.html|accessdate=28 April 2015|publisher=Die Welt|date=28 April 2015}}</ref> Thiago<ref name="Arjen Robben hurt in Bayern's loss, Robert Lewandowski concussed">{{cite news|title=Arjen Robben hurt in Bayern's loss, Robert Lewandowski concussed|url=http://www.espnfc.us/bayern-munich/story/2423774/arjen-robben-hurt-in-bayerns-lossrobert-lewandowski-concu|accessdate=29 April 2015|publisher=ESPN FC|date=28 April 2015}}</ref> and Lewandowski were also injured during the match.<ref name="Rein und raus – der bittere Abend des Arjen Robben"/> Lewandowski.<ref name="Arjen Robben hurt in Bayern's loss, Robert Lewandowski concussed"/> Robben was "ruled out" for the remainder of the season.<ref name="Bayern suffer Lewandowski, Robben injury blows after Dortmund defeat">{{cite news|last1=Uersfeld|first1=Stephan|title=Bayern suffer Lewandowski, Robben injury blows after Dortmund defeat|url=http://www.espnfc.us/bayern-munich/story/2424104/bayern-suffer-lewandowski-and-robben-blows|accessdate=29 April 2015|publisher=ESPN FC|date=29 April 2015}}</ref> Lewandowski sustained a concussion,<ref>{{cite news|title=Saison-Aus für Robben - Kieferbruch bei Lewandowski|url=http://www.kicker.de/news/fussball/bundesliga/startseite/626008/artikel_saison-aus-fuer-robben---kieferbruch-bei-lewandowski.html|accessdate=29 April 2015|publisher=kicker|date=29 April 2015|language=German}}</ref> broken jaw,<ref name="Bayern suffer Lewandowski, Robben injury blows after Dortmund defeat"/> and broken nose.<ref name="Bayern suffer Lewandowski, Robben injury blows after Dortmund defeat"/>

