====Suspensions====
The first suspension of the season was Jérôme Boateng when he was suspended for the last match of the [[2013–14 FC Bayern Munich season|2013–14 season]] and the first match of the 2014–15 season.<ref name="Boateng verpasst Saisonauftakt"/> The next Bayern suspension was [[Medhi Benatia]] which he had picked up in the [[2013–14 Coppa Italia]] with [[A.S. Roma|Roma]].<ref name="Altlasten aus Italien: Benatia im Pokal gesperrt"/> Benatia was again suspended after picking up a red card against [[Manchester City F.C.|Manchester City]] in Champions League.<ref name="Nach Rot: Medhi Benatia nur für ein Spiel gesperrt"/> He was given a one match ban.<ref name="Nach Rot: Medhi Benatia nur für ein Spiel gesperrt"/> Jérôme Boateng was suspended after picking up a red card against [[FC Schalke 04|Schalke 04]].<ref name="Bayern's Jerome Boateng handed three-match ban for Schalke red card">{{cite news|last1=Uersfeld|first1=Stephan|title=Bayern's Jerome Boateng handed three-match ban for Schalke red card|url=http://www.espnfc.com/bayern-munich/story/2283306/bayern-munich-defender-jerome-boateng-three-match-ban-schalke-red-card|accessdate=5 February 2015|publisher=ESPN FC|date=5 February 2015}}</ref> He was originally given a three-match ban.<ref name="Bayern's Jerome Boateng handed three-match ban for Schalke red card"/> However, after appeal,<ref name="Boateng drei Spiele gesperrt - Bayern legt Berufung ein">{{cite news|title=Boateng drei Spiele gesperrt - Bayern legt Berufung ein|trans-title=|url=http://www.augsburger-allgemeine.de/sport/fussball/Boateng-drei-Spiele-gesperrt-Bayern-legt-Berufung-ein-id32907087.html|accessdate=6 February 2015|publisher=Augsburger Allgemeine|date=5 February 2015|language=German}}</ref> the ban was reduced to two matches.<ref name="Sperre reduziert! Boateng fehlt nur noch einmal"/> [[Xabi Alonso]] was sent off for two bookable offences<ref name="Shakhtar Donetsk v Bayern Munich"/> and missed the return leg on 11 March.<ref name="Bayern Munich awakening from winter-break hibernation"/> Alonso also picked up his fifth yellow card against [[Hannover 96]] on 7 March<ref name=md24/> and was suspended<ref name=md24/> for the match against [[SV Werder Bremen|Werder Bremen]] on 14 March. During the match against Werder Bremen, Benatia picked up a fifth yellow card and was suspended for the match on 22 March against [[Borussia Mönchengladbach]].<ref name=md26/> Pepe Reina received a two-match suspension after his red card against [[FC Augsburg]].<ref name="Pepe Reina banned for two matches after Bayern Munich red card"/>

